		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://jlleblanc.com/articles/39-podcast-suite-version-10-stable"/>
		<published>2006-05-13T21:50:25Z</published>
		<updated>2006-05-13T21:50:25Z</updated>
		<id>http://jlleblanc.com/articles/39-podcast-suite-version-10-stable</id>
		<summary type="html">The Podcast Suite Version 1.0 is ready for download: &lt;a href=&quot;http://jlleblanc.com/com_podcast_v1.zip&quot;&gt;component&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://jlleblanc.com/mod_podcast_v1.zip&quot;&gt;module&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;http://jlleblanc.com/bot_podcast_v1.zip&quot;&gt;plugin&lt;/a&gt;. Thank you all for your testing, feedback, and encouragement! Here are some of the new features for version 1.0:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An integrated MP3 player, thanks to &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ericzhang.com/mp3.php&quot;&gt;Eric Zhang's player&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ID3 tag recognition, thanks to &lt;a href=&quot;http://phpclasses.spyral-productions.com/browse/package/1486.html&quot;&gt;Tadeu Oliveira's library&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adjustments to the module that let you override the link and image&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;{player ...} can now be used to add another instance of the Flash player or download link without adding another enclosure to the RSS feed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
If you are upgrading from Beta 4, simply uninstall the old component, module, and plugin and install the new ones. Otherwise, you should backup the podcast table in your database, do the reinstallation, then renew the database with the backup.</summary>
		<content type="html">The Podcast Suite Version 1.0 is ready for download: &lt;a href=&quot;http://jlleblanc.com/com_podcast_v1.zip&quot;&gt;component&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://jlleblanc.com/mod_podcast_v1.zip&quot;&gt;module&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;http://jlleblanc.com/bot_podcast_v1.zip&quot;&gt;plugin&lt;/a&gt;. Thank you all for your testing, feedback, and encouragement! Here are some of the new features for version 1.0:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An integrated MP3 player, thanks to &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ericzhang.com/mp3.php&quot;&gt;Eric Zhang's player&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ID3 tag recognition, thanks to &lt;a href=&quot;http://phpclasses.spyral-productions.com/browse/package/1486.html&quot;&gt;Tadeu Oliveira's library&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adjustments to the module that let you override the link and image&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;{player ...} can now be used to add another instance of the Flash player or download link without adding another enclosure to the RSS feed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
If you are upgrading from Beta 4, simply uninstall the old component, module, and plugin and install the new ones. Otherwise, you should backup the podcast table in your database, do the reinstallation, then renew the database with the backup.</content>
